          <actionDate>2018-09-27</actionDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Scarlett's Sunshine on Sudden Unexpected Death Act</b></p> <p>This bill establishes several programs and requirements relating to sudden unexpected infant death (SUID) and sudden unexplained death in childhood (SUDC). </p> <p>Among other things, the bill establishes grant programs to:</p> <ul> <li>promote comprehensive death scene investigations and autopsies relating to SUID and SUDC;</li> <li>improve infant and child death review programs; and</li> <li> promote education and outreach relating to SUID and SUDC.</li> </ul> <p>The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention must also study the use of genetic analysis and publish specified data regarding SUID and SUDC.</p>]]></text>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
